stylometry: RISKSIMTABLE allows me to vary the inputs in a simulations and generate a table which includes data such as the mean, standard deviation., minimum, and maximum. This is used to compare several simulations at once so it is easier for the user to compare different situations and make the best choice possible. A simulation model that I would use RISKSIMTABLE for is deciding how much of a product to produce given different demand possibilities. This is useful because depending on how much production costs are, it may be unclear how much to produce in order to make the greatest profit.
